OL,3,CMan wrongfully jailed for murder sees
OL,4,Ccompensation cut to cover 'jail
OL,5,Cexpenses'
OL,7,FA man whose name was cleared after
OL,8,Fspending more than 11 years in prison
OL,9,Fsays he's considering legal action
OL,10,Fover jail "living expenses".
OL,12,FMichael O'Brien was convicted of
OL,13,Fmurder in 1988 but his conviction was
OL,14,Fquashed in December 1999.
OL,16,FHe has since received compensation
OL,17,Ffrom the Home Office, but #37,500 was
OL,18,Fdeducted from his #600,000 payout for
OL,19,Fso-called "saved living expenses" from
OL,20,Fthe time he spent incarcerated.
