OL,3,CMan wrongfully jailed for murder sees
OL,4,Ccompensation cut to cover 'jail
OL,5,Cexpenses'
OL,7,FMichael O'Brien - who was 19 at the
OL,8,Ftime - told police that he and the
OL,9,Fother men had been out attempting to
OL,10,Fsteal cars on the night in question.
OL,12,FBut he claimed to have an alibi,
OL,13,Fproving that he couldn't have been at
OL,14,Fthe scene of the crime.
OL,16,FDespite this, he and the others were
OL,17,Fcharged with murder, with police later
OL,18,Frelying in court on a confession
OL,19,Fobtained from one of the men - Darren
OL,20,FHall - which was later found to be
OL,21,Funsafe.
