OL,3,CMan wrongfully jailed for murder sees
OL,4,Ccompensation cut to cover 'jail
OL,5,Cexpenses'
OL,7,FMichael O'Brien continued to protest
OL,8,Fhis innocence after he was jailed for
OL,9,Flife for murder.
OL,11,FIn 1999, he and the other members of
OL,12,Fthe "Cardiff Newsagent Three" were
OL,13,Fcleared at the Court of Appeal.
OL,15,FMr O'Brien later received #600,000 in
OL,16,Fcompensation from the Home Office, and
OL,17,Fa separate #300,000 from South Wales
OL,18,FPolice.
OL,20,FBut the scars of his wrongful
OL,21,Fconviction are still taking their toll.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/13
